gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 132, Hawks 121
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Giannis Antetokounmpo’s 1st triple-double of the season, the Bucks defeated the Hawks, 132-121. Antetokounmpo recorded 32 points, 11 rebounds and a season-high 10 assists for the Bucks in the victory, the 36th triple-double of his career, while Damian Lillard added 25 points, six rebounds and nine assists in the victory. Trae Young (32 points, 12 assists) and Dejounte Murray (30 points) combined for 62 points for the Hawks in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 14-6 on the season, while the Hawks fall to 9-10.
